--- title: "Datos abiertos" editor_options: chunk_output_type: console code-fold: true format: html: default --- ## Cat√°logo de datos en [datos.gob.mx](datos.gob.mx) ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} pacman::p_load(httr2, jsonlite, tidyverse, DT) req <- request("https://api.datos.gob.mx/v1/api-catalog?pageSize=8000") resp <- req_perform(req) dat_1 <- fromJSON(resp_body_string(resp)) dat_1_df <- dat_1$results for (i in 1:length(dat_1_df$variables)) { dat_1_df$variables[i] <- paste(dat_1_df$variables[[i]], collapse = ",") } dat_1_df$variables <- unlist(dat_1_df$variables) dat_1_df |> select("endpoint", "url", "variables") |> datatable() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: | ## Ozono | ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} url_O3 <- "https://api.datos.gob.mx/v2/sinaica?pageSize=8000¶metro=O3&estacionesid=259&page=1" req_O3 <- request(url_O3) resp_O3 <- req_perform(req_O3) dat_O3 <- fromJSON(resp_body_string(resp_O3)) dat_O3_df <- dat_O3$results ``` ::: Estos son los datos de ozono en la atm√≥sfera medidos en la estaci√≥n 259, de la Ciudad de M√©xico (@tbl-ozono). ::: {#tbl-ozono .cell .tbl-cap-location-top tbl-cap='Ozono atmosf√©rico'} ```{.r .cell-code} dat_O3_df |> select("fecha", "hora", "valororig") |> datatable(colnames = c("Fechca", "Hora", "Valor")) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: | ### Datos de estaciones meteorol√≥gicas Conagua | ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} url_meteo <- "https://smn.conagua.gob.mx/tools/RESOURCES/Normales_Climatologicas/Diarios/ver/dia30393.txt" dat_meteo_meta <- readLines(url_meteo, n = 25) # datos de la estaci√≥n estacion <- tibble(est = unlist(dat_meteo_meta[11:19])) estacion <- estacion |> mutate(var = str_extract(est, "(.*)(?=\\s:)"), val = str_extract(est, "(?<=\\s:)(.*)"), var = str_trim(var), val = str_trim(val), .keep = "unused" ) nombres <- estacion$var estacion <- as_tibble(t(estacion[, 2])) names(estacion) <- nombres # variables meteorologicas variables <- str_split(readLines(url_meteo, n = 24)[24], "\t")[[1]][c(1,3:6)] # datos meteorol√≥gicos dat_meteo <- read.csv(url_meteo, skip = 25, sep = "\t", header = F) names(dat_meteo) <- variables dat_meteo |> mutate(idEstacion = estacion$ESTACI√ìN) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} library(sf) # retrive a list of every layer of the kmz file l_layers <- sf::st_read("../EstacionesClimatologicas/doc.kml", "Estaciones operativas") l_layers$Description ``` :::
